-- Argentina Stock Movers: TGS and Banco Macro Were Active
-- B y   C a m i l a   R u s s o
-- 2012-06-22T20:23:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-22/argentina-stock-movers-tgs-banco-macro-are-active.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of the market close in
 Buenos Aires . The  Merval (MERVAL)  Index rose 1.3 percent to 2,341.49.  Transportadora de Gas del Sur SA  (TGSU2 AR) advanced 4.7
percent to 2.25 pesos. The natural gas distributor rose after
the country’s truck drivers yesterday ended a strike that
threatened to cut supply.  Banco Macro SA (BMA AF), Argentina’s largest lender by
market value, increased 4.1 percent to 8.35 pesos. Most
Argentine  government bonds  rose, boosting the value of banks’
fixed-income holdings.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Camila Russo in Buenos Aires at 
 crusso15@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  